Berkshire Hathaway, International Coal: U.S. Equity Preview

-- B y   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 
2011-05-06T22:44:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/berkshire-hathaway-international-coal-u-s-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in U.S. trading on May 9. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of 6:44 p.m. in  New York .  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A)  (BRK/A US): The insurance and
investment company led by billionaire Warren Buffett reported
first-quarter earnings excluding some items of $966 per Class A
share, less than the average analyst estimate of $1,149 a share
in a Bloomberg survey.  International Coal Group Inc. (ICO)  : The company, which
agreed to be purchased by Arch Coal Inc. this week, revised its
first-quarter results to a loss of $6.3 million from earnings of
$22 million, citing a loss in court to Allegheny Energy Supply.  Oncothyreon Inc. (ONTY)   climbed 6.7 percent to $4.77.
The developer of cancer treatments reported a first-quarter loss
excluding some items of 19 cents a share, more than the 18-cent
loss predicted by analysts on average.  Rosetta Resources Inc. (ROSE)  : The oil and natural gas
company reported first-quarter profit excluding some items of 21
cents a share, falling short of the 29-cent average estimate by
analysts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Inyoung Hwang in New York at 
 ihwang7@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 